source: Ah, it's her! Naran has chosen to return…
And then again… sometimes I wonder what will remain in the end?
And what if she fails… again?
But is it her destiny to create… a new Chorus?
But, how can that be!? Free will led to our terrible past; to endless war, famine and death.
Could her path be superior to our purified, unyielding measures?
How could I have missed this splendid possibility?
I always knew she was exceptional, but…
I wonder. Could humanity's faith in Naran hold strong and…
Naran acts as a defender of the weak. But she has set things in motion that surpass her intentions.
One formed through Naran's fight for free will?
Or is she simply our last trial before Chorus can finally be complete?
The Chorus, I sense a change… Why?
Yet she is unaware of the consequences and sacrifices that lie ahead.
… create a Chorus cleansed of my demons?
… to the world she left behind, the friend she abandoned, and the ancient Rites she tried to forget.
<IH1>And concede your free will in the choice.</>
<IH1>Better to be cautious about who you trust…</>
<IH1>I think that place is a myth.</>
<IH1>To survive defeat, focus on the mission…</>
<IH1>Took a long time to realize that. Too long…</>
<IH1>True… but the Rites could be affected as much by what we deny…</>
<IH1>… that I also miss, from time to time.</>
A Rite is always the same, but it's shaped by the individual's specific character.
Come from within you. They are a manifestation of your darkness. Attain the Chorus and let its light shine inside you.
I'm happy to share the Prophet's light.
Is it true that Rites manifest differently for each person?
Thanks for talking to me and my audience.
They only cleanse those who resist the Chorus.
Do you know Kirrim, from Enclave Security? We're looking for her.
Keep them off her. This process is fickle.
Okay. That barrier should be down.
What? How many of you monsters are there?
